title: 6th Street
creator: CDAR UIdaho

subject: sidewalk accessibilty; accessibility

title: Full Video - 6th Street
description: First-person view of entering Campus from 6th Street in an electric wheelchair

title: Problem Area 1 - 6th Street
description: The crossing here is rough and uneven, which makes driving over it with a mobility device difficult and damaging to the device

title: Problem Area 2 - 6th Street
description: Half of this sidewalk is inaccessible for mobility device users due to a metal covering that dips down low enough to create a significant vertical change. During busier hours, it can cause difficulty for all users to pass by

title: Problem Area 3 - 6th Street
description: A portion of the sidewalk is damaged, which creates difficulty when crossing for mobility aid users, and it is best to avoid it by going around it as the videographer does

title: Problem Area 4 - 6th Street
description: Another portion of the sidewalk is damaged, creating a challenging experience for those with mobility devices to cross over and cannot be maneuvered around

title: Problem Area 5 - 6th Street
description: A crack across the sidewalk is jarring for those using mobility aids

Deakin Avenue
creator: CDAR UIdaho
description: First-person view of traveling down Deakin Avenue in an electric wheelchair
subject: sidewalk accessibilty; accessibility

title: Full Video - Deakin Avenue
description: First-person view of traveling down Deakin Avenue in an electric wheelchair

title: Problem Area 1 - Deakin Avenue
description: Intersection with vertical change preventing access on and off the sidewalk

title: Problem Area 2 - Deakin Avenue
description: Sharp and narrow curb ramp makes access on and off the sidewalk dangerous

title: Problem Area 3 - Deakin Avenue
description: Fragmented sidewalks are inaccessible and rough for mobility aid users

title: Problem Area 4 - Deakin Avenue
description: Vertical change which leads to no way back if crossed over and leads to a diagonal and narrow path, which is risky when leaves or ice/snow is involved

title: Problem Area 5 - Deakin Avenue
description: Steep vertical change risks injury for mobility aid users and those with assistive devices, especially if obscured by leaves or ice/snow

title: Problem Area 6 - Deakin Avenue
description: Gaps between sidewalks and brick layouts contain multiple verticle changes, which is rough for those using mobility aids such as scooters, wheelchairs, and other such devices and adds extra wear and tear

title: Problem Area 7 - Deakin Avenue
description: A vertical change on one end makes traveling across difficult for those operating mobility aid devices

Elm Street
creator: CDAR UIdaho
description: First-person view of traveling down Elm Street in an electric wheelchair
subject: sidewalk accessibilty; accessibility

title: Full Video - Elm Street
description: First-person view of traveling down Elm Street in an electric wheelchair

title: Problem Area 1 - Elm Street
description: The sidewalk slabs are tilted either left or right and will veer off anyone in those directions who tries to progress down the sidewalk using a mobility aid

title: Problem Area 2 - Elm Street
description: The curb ramp leading to the intersection is sloped and narrow, which will push mobility aid users toward the street, and it is easy to lose control of direction

title: Problem Area 3 - Elm Street
description: Very sharp ramp on/off and mobility aid users may lose control and be veered off in directions that could lead them into the street

title: Problem Area 4 - Elm Street
description: Here, we see a vertical change that most mobility aid users may be stopped at; the videographer was able to clear it

title: Problem Area 5 - Elm Street
description: The videographer cannot continue down the sidewalk due to the sidewalk being completely destroyed

title: Problem Area 6 - Elm Street
description: A vertical change prevents mobility aid users from progressing in either direction of the sidewalk; this section contains many minor but potentially damaging vertical changes and should be avoided for people with disabilities

Idaho Avenue
creator: CDAR UIdaho
description: First-person view of traveling down Idaho Avenue in an electric wheelchair
subject: sidewalk accessibilty; accessibility

title: Full Video - Idaho Avenue
description: First-person view of traveling down Idaho Avenue in an electric wheelchair

title: Problem Area 1 - Idaho Avenue
description: Ramping on/off can be difficult in winter weather or if leaves cover the ground. Compounding with the sharp angle of the on/off ramp, these situations of weather/coverings can veer mobility aid users into the street or off the curb. It is located at the intersection of Elm Street and Idaho Avenue

title: Problem Area 2 - Idaho Avenue
description: The sidewalk in this segment isn't very wide for larger wheelchairs, which mobility aid users should avoid due to the potential of tipping into the street or lawn area. Using the other sidewalk opposite this narrow path would be safer and should be used instead

title: Problem Area 3 - Idaho Avenue
description: This section has two on/off ramps, which are rough to ride on and awkward to use

title: Problem Area 4 - Idaho Avenue
description: The on/off ramp in this street crossing is sharp and can cause mobility aid users to lose control and veer off towards the street or curb

title: Problem Area 5 - Idaho Avenue
description: This section of sidewalk is destroyed but offers a path forward if the mobility aid user goes to the right. However, if covered in leaves or snow, it can cause those unaware to get stuck or potentially damage their device

title: Problem Area 6 - Idaho Avenue
description: There is a sewage lid that is rough around the edges and contains many bumps and gaps

title: Problem Area 7 - Idaho Avenue
description: A vertical change prevents the mobility aid user from progressing down the sidewalk but could be crossed by those going up the sidewalk

Kibbie Dome Route (Idaho Ave. and Stadium Drive)
creator: CDAR UIdaho
description: First-person view of traveling down two entrances into the Kibbie Dome in an electric wheelchair
subject: sidewalk accessibilty; accessibility

title: Full Video - Kibbie Dome Route
description: First-person view of traveling down two entrances into the Kibbie Dome in an electric wheelchair

title: Problem Area 1 - Kibbie Dome Route
description: When traveling the sidewalk towards the Kibbie Dome off Idaho Ave. and Rayburn Street, there is no access to stay on the sidewalk, meaning mobility aid users and other people with disabilities travel in the street, which presents risk as there is a blindspot when vehicles turn the corner in this area. However, many people still walk the road during game days, which implies the risk is less severe but is a concern nonetheless

title: Problem Area 2 - Kibbie Dome Route
description: The ramp on/off in this area is narrow and steep, which can be difficult for those with mobility aids

title: Problem Area 3 - Kibbie Dome Route
description: The ramp on/off has a gap between the street and the entrance onto the sidewalk, which can cause mobility aid users to get stuck

Sweet Avenue

description: First-person view of traveling down Sweet Avenue in an electric wheelchair
subject: sidewalk accessibilty; accessibility

title: Full Video - Sweet Avenue
description: First-person view of traveling down Sweet Avenue in an electric wheelchair

title: Problem Area 1 - Sweet Avenue
description: The entrance area that cuts into the sidewalk makes it steep and will pull those using mobility devices into the street

title: Problem Area 2 - Sweet Avenue
description: A gap here makes access difficult and leads to a steep slant that can lead someone using a mobility aid into the street

title: Problem Area 3 - Sweet Avenue
description: The ramp on/off for both entries in the crossing of Deakin and Sweet has gaps between the street and the entry points, which is challenging for mobility aid users to maneuver

title: Problem Area 4 - Sweet Avenue
description: When passed over, a vertical change here will prevent those using mobility aids from returning the same way

title: Problem Area 5 - Sweet Avenue
description: This section of the sidewalk is damaged, making crossing difficult and damaging to the mobility device; the videographer travels to the left to avoid it

title: Problem Area 6 - Sweet Avenue
description: Here, this section of the sidewalk is fractured and rough to drive over for mobility aid users

title: Problem Area 7 - Sweet Avenue
description: There is a vertical change here that prevented the videographer from passing. If someone did pass this point, another, more considerable, vertical change would stop any mobility aid user from passing
